vulnerability.name: USN-5785-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that FreeRADIUS incorrectly handled multiple EAP-pwd handshakes. An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service. This issue only affected Ubuntu 18.04 LTS. (CVE-2019-17185)  Shane Guan discovered that FreeRADIUS incorrectly handled memory when checking unknown SIM option sent by EAP-SIM supplicant. An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service on the server. This issue only affected Ubuntu 16.04 ESM, Ubuntu 18.04 LTS and Ubuntu 20.04 LTS. (CVE-2022-41860)  It was discovered that FreeRADIUS incorrectly handled memory when processing certain abinary attributes. An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service on the server. (CVE-2022-41861)

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in FreeRADIUS.
